    "narrative_summary": "The NTHL1 S5C (Ser5Cys) missense change is the only variant described in the supplied data. No disease associations for this alteration are mentioned in the extracted evidence. The single article identified (PMCID\u00a0PMC6018746) focuses on PRMT5 inhibition and the p53\u2011MDM4 axis and does not provide any interpretative information about the NTHL1 S5C variant, nor does it report clinical case data, segregation analyses, or a classification of pathogenicity.\n\nClinical evidence for the S5C substitution is absent; the source contains no case reports, family studies, or diagnostic classifications that involve this NTHL1 change [PMC6018746].\n\nFunctional evidence is likewise lacking. The extracted material does not describe in\u2011vitro or in\u2011vivo experiments assessing the impact of the Ser5Cys substitution on NTHL1 protein function, DNA repair activity, or related cellular phenotypes [PMC6018746].\n\nPopulation frequency and computational predictions are not provided in the available excerpt, and no allele\u2011frequency databases or in\u2011silico scores are cited for this variant [PMC6018746].\n\nIn summary, the current literature excerpt offers no data to support a pathogenic or benign interpretation of the NTHL1 S5C variant. Consequently, its clinical significance remains uncertain and it should be regarded as a variant of uncertain significance pending further evidence.",
